title: Experience Shoreline: An Information Session for Prospective Students
description:
Individuals* interested in attending Shoreline Community College will be able to ask questions and learn about:
  • The admission process
  • Types of financial aid
  • College degrees and certificates offered
  • Academic and personal resources available
  • This session include a campus tour
And more…

Reserve your spot by filling out a sign-up form.


*For high school classes or other groups, please contact Amy Stapleton at astaplet@shoreline.edu or .

title: START (Student Advising and Registration Time)
description:
If you are new to Shoreline and intend to take classes Fall Quarter, you should attend a START session. Fall Quarter begins on September 25th.

During this session you will:
• meet with a general academic advisor
• discuss degree options
• register for classes


Reserve your spot by filling out a sign-up form.

Reminder: You will need a student ID
